---
import PublicLayout from '../layouts/PublicLayout.astro'
import { SITE_URL } from '../lib/site'
---
<PublicLayout
  title="Privacy — DegreeWiki"
  description="How DegreeWiki handles account data, Fit Finder preferences, AI feature logs, and cookies."
  canonical={SITE_URL + '/privacy'}
>
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">

    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Privacy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-8">
      DegreeWiki is in early development. This privacy statement covers current data practices
      and will be expanded as the platform grows.
    </p>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What data we collect</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Account data.</span> If you create an account,
          we store your email address via Supabase Auth. We may also store a display name if you
          provide one.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Fit Finder preferences.</span> If you use
          Fit Finder while logged in, we store your study preferences — including target degree
          level, subjects of interest, preferred countries, and budget range — so you can return
          to your results. These preferences are linked to your account and are not shared
          publicly.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Session data.</span> We use session cookies
          provided by Supabase Auth to keep you signed in. These are functional cookies required
          for authentication.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">What data we do not collect</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-600">
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>We do not collect payment or billing data.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>We do not sell your data to third parties.</li>
        <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-gray-400 shrink-0">&mdash;</span>We do not currently use advertising trackers, retargeting pixels, or third-party analytics on this site.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">AI features</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        When you use AI-assisted features on DegreeWiki (such as the Fit Finder AI summary),
        your query is logged server-side with your user ID, session type, model used, and
        token count. This data is used for rate limiting and cost management only.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        Fit Finder match results are saved to your account so you can review them later.
        Saved results include the ranked program matches and, if generated, the AI summary
        from that session. You can delete saved results from your account at any time.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-3">
        If you use saved-result AI chat or future AI chat features, your questions and AI
        responses may be stored with your account so the conversation can be shown again
        later or cleared by you.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        AI-assisted features send relevant session context to an external AI provider
        (currently Google Gemini) to generate summaries. We do not sell this data or use
        it for advertising.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Third-party services</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-600">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Supabase.</span> Account data, Fit Finder
          preferences, and session data are stored on Supabase infrastructure. See
          <a href="https://supabase.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">supabase.com/privacy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Cloudflare.</span> DegreeWiki is delivered via
          Cloudflare Pages and Workers. Cloudflare may log request metadata as part of normal
          CDN and security operations. See
          <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">cloudflare.com/privacypolicy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium text-gray-700">Cloudinary (future).</span> Images and media
          may be delivered via Cloudinary CDN when media features are enabled.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Cookies</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        We use session cookies provided by Supabase Auth to keep you signed in. These are
        functional cookies. We do not currently use advertising or tracking cookies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Data deletion</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        A public contact and correction channel will be added before launch. Until then, users
        should verify important details directly with official sources. Data deletion requests
        received through any available contact channel will be handled within a reasonable
        timeframe.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3">Changes to this statement</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
        This privacy statement may be updated as features are added. Significant changes will be
        reflected in the "Last updated" date at the top of this page.
      </p>
    </section>

    <div class="mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-gray-100 flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm">
      <a href="/about"      class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">About</a>
      <a href="/disclaimer" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Disclaimer</a>
      <a href="/terms"      class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Terms of Use</a>
    </div>

  </div>
</PublicLayout>
